author: kfogel
msg: Factor duplicated code, handle keywords in the detranslation routine:
* subversion/libsvn_wc/adm_crawler.c (do_postfix_text_deltas): Just
use svn_wc_translated_file.  Move some stuff into the hash walk scope.
(do_apply_textdelta): Doc fix.
(struct target_baton): Add documentation.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/util.c (svn_wc_translated_file): Handle
keywords too, and fix a bug in the eol handling.

author: brane
msg: Add new files to Win32 build.
* subversion/clients/cmdline/subversion_client.dsp: Added propedit-cmd.c.
* subversion/libsvn_client/libsvn_client.dsp: Added ra.c.

author: sussman
msg: Begin adding keyword logic to existing EOL logic for checkouts/updates.
* get_editor.c (struct file_baton): add two new fields to file_baton
for detecting any keyword propchange during the update.
(change_file_prop): cache any keyword propchange received during update.
(close_file): carefully decide which value of 'svn:keywords' to use
during textual merge, by pre-emptively looking for property
conflicts, and possibly writing out a newly-received value a bit
early.

author: kfogel
msg: This fixes diff_tests.py 5 and 6, which commit 856 broke:
* subversion/libsvn_wc/diff.c (close_file): Use the same err variable
for both diff commands, so it's sure to be initialized by the time we
check it.
